RECENT developments have hit Mzansi people where it hurts most – in their pockets. An unstable economy, crime, as well as record high and soaring prices are leaving people of SunLand concerned about their future. Joseph Mswane (45) from Fleurhoff told SunMoney: “It’s very tough and my worry is that it seems like things are getting worse.” He said while he and his wife had cut down on monthly expenditure including groceries, most of his friends were really struggling. “We used to buy R3 000 groceries,” said Joseph. “We’ve had to buy less now and cut down on entertainment. “We’re no longer going out as often as we used to. “Staying indoors and partying at home saves us money.” Here are financial expert Eric Streso’s tips on how to survive the tough economic climate.